\section{Mayer-Vietoris LES short-exact infrastructure (iter-020)}
\label{sec:hmodule_prime_mayer_vietoris_short_exact}

After Section~\ref{sec:hmodule_prime_mayer_vietoris_short_exact} (sic --- self-reference; properly: after the previous section, which gave us $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex$, $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}$, and the helper instance $(\ModuleCat.\free\,k).\mathtt{IsLeftAdjoint}$) iter-020 lands the next coherent cohort: the categorical-exactness instances on the iter-019 short complex, mirroring Mathlib \texttt{MayerVietorisSquare.lean} L251--268 line-by-line for the $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor.

\subsection{The second Mathlib gap: $(\ModuleCat.\free\,k).\PreservesMonomorphisms$}
\label{sec:hmodule_prime_module_free_preserves_mono_gap}

Mathlib's \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/Grp/Adjunctions.lean} registers the instance \lstinline{AddCommGrpCat.instPreservesMonomorphismsFree : AddCommGrpCat.free.PreservesMonomorphisms}. The corresponding instance for the $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavour is \emph{absent} from \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/ModuleCat/Adjunctions.lean}. Without it, after \lstinline{simp only [biprod.lift_snd]} the residual goal $\mathtt{Mono}\,(-(\presheafToSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathtt{map}\,(\mathtt{Functor.whiskerRight}\,(\yoneda.\mathtt{map}\,S.f_{13})\,(\ModuleCat.\free\,k)))$ cannot be discharged by \lstinline{infer_instance} (probe-verified by the iter-020 plan-agent: synthesis fails outright).

\begin{definition}[Helper instance: $\ModuleCat.\free\,k$ preserves monomorphisms (iter-020)]
  \label{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_preservesMonomorphisms}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.ModuleCat_free_preservesMonomorphisms}
  \uses{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_isLeftAdjoint}
  Working over a field $k$, the free-module functor $\ModuleCat.\free\,k : \mathrm{Type}\,u \to \ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k$ preserves monomorphisms: for any injective function $f : X \to Y$ between types, $(\ModuleCat.\free\,k).\mathtt{map}\,f$ is injective on $\Finsupp\,X\,k$.
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  Mathlib's \lstinline{Finsupp.mapDomain_injective} (\texttt{Mathlib/Data/Finsupp/Basic.lean}) provides the underlying-set-level proof: if $f : X \to Y$ is injective, then $\Finsupp.\mathtt{mapDomain}\,f : \Finsupp\,X\,k \to \Finsupp\,Y\,k$ is injective. Combined with $\ModuleCat.\mathtt{mono\_iff\_injective}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/ModuleCat/EpiMono.lean}) bridging \lstinline{Mono} in $\ModuleCat\,k$ to underlying-set injectivity, and $\CategoryTheory.\mathtt{mono\_iff\_injective}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Types/Basic.lean}) bridging \lstinline{Mono} in $\mathrm{Type}\,u$ to underlying-set injectivity, the preservation predicate reduces to a four-line tactic block. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-020) confirms it typechecks end-to-end against current Mathlib + post-iter-019 project state, kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\subsection{$\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex$ is short exact}
\label{sec:hmodule_prime_short_exact}

\begin{lemma}[$\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.f$ is mono (iter-020)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_f_mono}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_shortComplex_f_mono}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex, def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_preservesMonomorphisms}
  Under the standing typeclass assumptions, $(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).f$ is a monomorphism in $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib L251--257 with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free \to \ModuleCat.\free\,k$. The proof is a tactic block: it suffices to show $\mathtt{Mono}\,((\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).f \circ \mathtt{biprod.snd})$ (then conclude by \lstinline{mono_of_mono _ biprod.snd}). After \lstinline{dsimp} unfolds the structure-literal projection and \lstinline{simp only [biprod.lift_snd]} extracts the right-hand component, the goal reduces to $\mathtt{Mono}\,(-(\presheafToSheaf\,J\,\_).\mathtt{map}\,(\mathtt{Functor.whiskerRight}\,(\yoneda.\mathtt{map}\,S.f_{13})\,(\ModuleCat.\free\,k)))$, which \lstinline{infer_instance} discharges via \lstinline{Functor.PreservesMonomorphisms} composition (using Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_preservesMonomorphisms}, \lstinline{presheafToSheaf}'s exactness, \lstinline{yoneda}'s mono-preservation, and the underlying \lstinline{Mono S.f_{13}} from $S$'s Mayer-Vietoris-square pullback condition). The whole proof requires the attribute \lstinline{set_option backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in} (mirrors Mathlib L251) so the typeclass-search engine is willing to unfold the necessary definitional steps. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-020) confirms the body typechecks end-to-end, kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.g$ is epi (iter-020)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_g_epi}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_shortComplex_g_epi}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}
  Under the standing typeclass assumptions, $(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).g$ is an epimorphism in $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib L259--261 with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free \to \ModuleCat.\free\,k$. The proof is a one-line term-mode body: by the iter-019 lemma $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}\,k\,S$ (Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}), the pushout square's cokernel-cofork is a colimit cocone for $g$, which by $\mathtt{ShortComplex.exact\_and\_epi\_g\_iff\_g\_is\_cokernel}$ (Mathlib \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Exact.lean}) implies $g$ is an epi. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-020) confirms the body typechecks end-to-end, kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex$ is exact (iter-020)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_exact}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_shortComplex_exact}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}
  Under the standing typeclass assumptions, $(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).\Exact$ holds: the kernel of $g$ equals the image of $f$ in $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib L263--265 with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free \to \ModuleCat.\free\,k$. The proof is a one-line term-mode body: by $\mathtt{ShortComplex.exact\_of\_g\_is\_cokernel}$ (Mathlib \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/ShortComplex/Exact.lean}) it suffices to exhibit a colimit-cocone witness for $g$ as a cokernel, which is exactly $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{isPushoutModuleCatFreeSheaf}\,k\,S$'s $\mathtt{isColimitCokernelCofork}$ accessor. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-020) confirms the body typechecks end-to-end, kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[$\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex$ is short exact (iter-020)]
  \label{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_shortExact}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'_shortComplex_shortExact}
  \uses{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_f_mono, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_g_epi, lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_exact}
  Under the standing typeclass assumptions, $(\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\,k\,S).\ShortExact$ holds: the short complex is short exact (i.e.\ the three predicates $f$-mono, $g$-epi, exact-at-the-middle hold simultaneously).
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib L267--268 with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free \to \ModuleCat.\free\,k$. The proof is a one-line anonymous-constructor: the $\mathtt{ShortExact}$ structure has only the $\Exact$ predicate as a non-trivial field (the $\mathtt{Mono}\,f$ and $\mathtt{Epi}\,g$ predicates are typeclass-resolved from Lemmas~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_f_mono} and \ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_g_epi}), so the only thing to fill is $\mathtt{exact} := \HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\_\mathtt{exact}\,k\,S$ from Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_exact}. Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-020) confirms the body typechecks end-to-end, kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{remark}[Why iter-020 lays exactly these five declarations]
  Mathlib's connecting hom $\delta$ for the Mayer-Vietoris LES (\texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L112--114) reads
  \[
    \delta \;:=\; \mathtt{AddCommGrpCat.ofHom}\,(S.\mathtt{shortComplex\_shortExact}.\mathtt{extClass}.\mathtt{precomp}\,\_\,(\mathtt{by\ omega})),
  \]
  consuming $S.\mathtt{shortComplex\_shortExact}.\mathtt{extClass}$ where $\mathtt{extClass} : \Ext\,A\,B\,1$ is the extension class associated with a $\mathtt{ShortExact}$ structure (\texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/DerivedCategory/Ext/ExactSequences.lean}). To obtain a $\ModuleCat\,k$-flavored $\delta$ in iter-021+, we need iter-020's $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\_\mathtt{shortExact}$ as input. The five declarations of this section build it bottom-up:
  \begin{enumerate}
    \item Helper instance $(\ModuleCat.\free\,k).\PreservesMonomorphisms$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_ModuleCat_free_preservesMonomorphisms}) — Mathlib gap-fill, mirrors $\AddCommGrpCat$'s registered instance.
    \item $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.f$ is mono (Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_f_mono}) — direct consumer of the helper.
    \item $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.g$ is epi (Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_g_epi}) — consumer of the iter-019 pushout lemma.
    \item $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.\Exact$ (Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_exact}) — also consumer of the iter-019 pushout lemma; sibling of (3).
    \item $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex.\ShortExact$ (Lemma~\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_shortComplex_shortExact}) — packaging of (2)+(3)+(4).
  \end{enumerate}
  All five bodies are probe-confirmed at one-line term-mode or short-tactic forms; they form the smallest useful unit on the LES infrastructure path because they jointly yield $\HModulePrime\_\shortComplex\_\mathtt{shortExact}$, the carrier consumed by iter-021+ for the $\delta$ connecting hom. The iter-020 sorry-count trajectory is $9 \to 13 \to 9$ (four new \lstinline{sorry} sites — one each in the $\mathtt{Mono}$, $\mathtt{Epi}$, $\Exact$, $\ShortExact$ declarations; the helper instance has its body inline because the proof is a structural four-line tactic block, no \lstinline{sorry} needed). All filled in the iter-020 prover round.
\end{remark}

